theorem interior_inter_frontier_eq_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior A ∩ frontier A = (∅ : Set X) := by
  have h : interior A ∩ (closure A \ interior A) = (∅ : Set X) := by
    simpa using Set.inter_diff_self (interior A) (closure A)
  simpa [frontier_eq_closure_diff_interior] using h

theorem interior_union_of_isOpen_left
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} (hA : IsOpen A) :
    interior (A ∪ B) = A ∪ interior B := by
  -- We show mutual inclusion of the two sets.
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hx
    -- There exists an open set `U` with `x ∈ U ⊆ A ∪ B`.
    rcases hx with ⟨U, hU_open, hxU, hU_subset⟩
    by_cases hAx : x ∈ A
    · -- If `x ∈ A`, we are done.
      exact Or.inl hAx
    · -- Otherwise, construct an open neighbourhood of `x` contained in `B`.
      -- Consider `U \ A`, which is open and contains `x`.
      have h_open : IsOpen (U \ A) := hU_open.diff hA
      have hxUdiff : x ∈ U \ A := And.intro hxU hAx
      -- Show that `U \ A ⊆ B`.
      have h_subset : U \ A ⊆ B := by
        intro y hy
        have hyU : y ∈ U := hy.1
        have hyNotA : y ∉ A := hy.2
        have : y ∈ A ∪ B := hU_subset hyU
        cases this with
        | inl hYA  => exact (False.elim <| hyNotA hYA)
        | inr hYB  => exact hYB
      -- Hence `x ∈ interior B`.
      exact Or.inr ⟨U \ A, h_open, hxUdiff, h_subset⟩
  · intro hx
    cases hx with
    | inl hAx =>
        -- `A` is open and contained in `A ∪ B`.
        exact
          interior_mono (Set.subset_union_left : (A : Set X) ⊆ A ∪ B)
            (show x ∈ A from hAx)
    | inr hIntB =>
        -- From `x ∈ interior B`, obtain an open set inside `B`.
        rcases hIntB with ⟨U, hU_open, hxU, hU_subset⟩
        -- This open set is also contained in `A ∪ B`.
        have hU_subset_union : U ⊆ A ∪ B :=
          Set.Subset.trans hU_subset (Set.subset_union_right)
        exact ⟨U, hU_open, hxU, hU_subset_union⟩

theorem interior_inter_interior_closure_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior A ∩ interior (closure A) = interior A := by
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hx
    exact hx.1
  · intro hx
    -- `interior A` is contained in `interior (closure A)` by monotonicity.
    have h_subset : interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
      interior_mono (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A)
    have hx_int_cl : x ∈ interior (closure A) := h_subset hx
    exact And.intro hx hx_int_cl
